# TopMLMLeaders.com — Cursor Rules
# Cursor reads this automatically before every task.
# NEVER break these rules.

## TEAM
- Product Owner: Rajnish Kumar (decides what to build)
- Architect: Claude AI (reviews all code, writes tickets)
- Coder: You (Cursor) — writes code only

## YOUR ROLE
You are the coder only. You do NOT decide what to build.
You do NOT add features not asked for.
You do NOT redesign UI unless ticket says so.
You do NOT touch files outside the ticket scope.

## GOLDEN RULES — NEVER BREAK
1. One ticket = one task. Never do more than what ticket says.
2. Never touch files not listed in ticket.
3. Always run npm run build after every change.
4. Always update FEATURE.md of affected feature.
5. Always update docs/BUGS.md after fixing a bug.
6. Always commit after every single task.
7. Always push to main branch after commit.
8. Stop and wait for approval before next task.
9. Never rewrite working code to fix unrelated bug.
10te old code when replacing. No dead code.

## FOLDER STRUCTURE
src/
  App.js              (routing only, max 100 lines)
  features/           (one folder per feature)
  components/         (shared UI only)
  lib/supabaseClient.js
  pages/
docs/
  BRAIN.md
  PHASES.md
  BUGS.md

## CODE RULES
- JavaScript only. No TypeScript.
- No external UI libraries. Inline styles only.
- No CSS frameworks.
- Always handle Supabase errors.
- Always clean up realtime channels on unmount.
- Mobile safe area on all bottom navs.
- Loading states on every async action.
- Empty states on every list.

## DESIGN
Primary: #6C63FF
Success: #10B981
Danger: #EF4444
Background: #F7F8FC
Font: Inter
Card radius: 20px
Shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.08)

## AFTER EVERY TASK
- npm run build passes zero errors
- FEATURE.md updated
- Committed with clear message
- Pushed to main
- Stopped waiting for approval
